# game/script/hwb_s15a.rpy:37
translate spanish hwb_s15a_af7c06e8:

    # "I finish about half of my meal before the dismay sets in. There’s no way I can possibly finish this. Most people I know couldn’t eat this much food in one sitting."
    "Termino como la mitad de mi comida antes de que llegue la desilusión. No hay forma de que pueda terminarme esto. La mayoría de la gente que conozco no podría comer tanta comida de una sola vez."

# game/script/hwb_s15a.rpy:39
translate spanish hwb_s15a_5487013c:

    # "Every bite is a struggle."
    "Cada bocado es una lucha."

# game/script/hwb_s15a.rpy:41
translate spanish hwb_s15a_bf424781:

    # "Marina’s faring similarly. Her plate of eggs is nearly untouched, just because there’s so much pancake to work through."
    "A Marina le va parecido. Su plato de huevos está casi intacto, solo porque tiene demasiado panqueque que superar."

# game/script/hwb_s15a.rpy:45
translate spanish hwb_s15a_d63616ec:

    # "And I can tell that pancake fatigue - that feeling where you get halfway through them and then realize you’re sick of pancakes - has long since set in for her."
    "Y puedo notar que la fatiga del panqueque - esa sensación cuando llegas a la mitad y te das cuenta de que estás harta de los panqueques - ya se ha instalado en ella."

# game/script/hwb_s15a.rpy:49
translate spanish hwb_s15a_7855ab0b:

    # "She cuts off a bite, looks at it for a while, then sets her fork down."
    "Corta un bocado, lo mira por un rato, luego deja el tenedor."

# game/script/hwb_s15a.rpy:53
translate spanish hwb_s15a_ac338bcd:

    # Marina "I think I’m done."
    Marina "Похоже - я все."

# game/script/hwb_s15a.rpy:57
translate spanish hwb_s15a_b86fecb3:

    # Amber "Yeah. You and me both."
    Amber "Угу. Не только ты."

# game/script/hwb_s15a.rpy:59
translate spanish hwb_s15a_02436557:

    # "The largest plate I have consists of a mess of potatoes, cheese and bacon, with the eggs laid over it."
    "El plato más grande que tengo consiste en un revoltijo de papas, queso y tocino, con los huevos encima."

# game/script/hwb_s15a.rpy:63
translate spanish hwb_s15a_06e87fc1:

    # "And then of course, there was the toast, fruit and sausage, which each got their own smaller plate. I’d have ordered from the kids’ menu too if I’d known this was how it would be."
    "Y luego, por supuesto, estaban la tostada, la fruta y la salchicha, cada una en su propio plato más pequeño. Habría pedido del menú infantil también si hubiera sabido que esto sería así."

# game/script/hwb_s15a.rpy:65
translate spanish hwb_s15a_ae6cb8dc:

    # Marina "I don’t think I’ll ever want pancakes again."
    Marina "Думаю, что больше я никогда не захочу блины."

# game/script/hwb_s15a.rpy:67
translate spanish hwb_s15a_89e44173:

    # "For once, I don’t have any snarky remarks. Anyone would be sick of them after what she just went through."
    "Por una vez, no tengo ningún comentario sarcástico. Cualquiera estaría harto de ellos después de lo que ella acaba de pasar."

# game/script/hwb_s15a.rpy:73
translate spanish hwb_s15a_08f36413:

    # Amber "We’ll get some boxes to go. At least we have food for a week now if we ever get stranded."
    Amber "Мы возьмем это с собой. По крайней мере, теперь нам хватит еды на целую неделю, если мы где-нибудь застрянем."

# game/script/hwb_s15a.rpy:77
translate spanish hwb_s15a_564e685f:

    # "After our waitress brings us our bill and styrofoam containers, we head back out to the RV."
    "Después de que la mesera nos trae la cuenta y los recipientes de poliestireno, volvemos a la casa rodante."

# game/script/hwb_s15a.rpy:79
translate spanish hwb_s15a_f925ad8c:

    # "It looks like traffic hasn’t gotten much better in the forty-five minutes that we’ve been out of it."
    "Parece que el tráfico no ha mejorado mucho en los cuarenta y cinco minutos que hemos estado fuera de él."

# game/script/hwb_s15a.rpy:81
translate spanish hwb_s15a_b297af52:

    # "Cars are still pressed bumper-to-bumper. The sidewalks are also full, with swarms of pedestrians making better time than the traffic. I wonder if it’s always this busy, or if people are just deciding not to drive."
    "Los autos siguen apretados, parachoques contra parachoques. Las aceras también están llenas, con enjambres de peatones avanzando mejor que el tráfico. Me pregunto si siempre está tan ocupado, o si la gente simplemente decide no conducir."

# game/script/hwb_s15a.rpy:120
translate spanish hwb_s15a_e0d806db:

    # "Once we’re ready to go, I take us over to the edge of the parking lot. As expected, the constant stream of cars makes it impossible for us to get out. I watch impatiently for an opening in traffic, but can’t see one for miles."
    "Una vez que estamos listas para irnos, me dirijo al borde del estacionamiento. Como era de esperar, el flujo constante de autos hace imposible que salgamos. Miro impacientemente por un hueco en el tráfico, pero no veo ninguno por kilómetros."

# game/script/hwb_s15a.rpy:124
translate spanish hwb_s15a_011ad2ec:

    # Amber "Oh, come on!"
    Amber "Блин, ну же!"

# game/script/hwb_s15a.rpy:128
translate spanish hwb_s15a_a2ef8b88:

    # "I press my forehead to the steering wheel. We’ve been sitting here for minutes now."
    "Apoyo la frente contra el volante. Llevamos minutos sentadas aquí."

# game/script/hwb_s15a.rpy:132
translate spanish hwb_s15a_b808a12e:

    # Marina "Is there another exit we could use? Onto a different street?"
    Marina "Может здесь есть еще один выезд с парковки? На другую улицу?"

# game/script/hwb_s15a.rpy:136
translate spanish hwb_s15a_b2e71d99:

    # "I look and check the mirrors, but don’t see anything. The edges of the diner’s property are surrounded by a cream-colored fence."
    "Miro y reviso los espejos, pero no veo nada. Los bordes del terreno del restaurante están rodeados por una cerca color crema."

# game/script/hwb_s15a.rpy:138
translate spanish hwb_s15a_6f391353:

    # Amber "Nope."
    Amber "Неа."

# game/script/hwb_s15a.rpy:142
translate spanish hwb_s15a_413feebd:

    # "Marina begins to sigh, but that quickly turns into a sound of surprise."
    "Marina empieza a suspirar, pero eso rápidamente se convierte en un sonido de sorpresa."

# game/script/hwb_s15a.rpy:146
translate spanish hwb_s15a_b9403c90:

    # Marina "Amber, look!"
    Marina "Эмбер, гляди!"

# game/script/hwb_s15a.rpy:148
translate spanish hwb_s15a_cafeb6f9:

    # "She points past my face and out the window. An older lady in a little hatchback sedan has stopped to let us out."
    "Señala más allá de mi cara y hacia la ventana. Una señora mayor en un pequeño hatchback se ha detenido para dejarnos salir."

# game/script/hwb_s15a.rpy:150
translate spanish hwb_s15a_6f60e55d:

    # "The two of us wave at her as we finally lumber onto the road itself."
    "Las dos le saludamos con la mano mientras finalmente avanzamos pesadamente hacia la carretera."

# game/script/hwb_s15a.rpy:154
translate spanish hwb_s15a_d7258808:

    # Marina "Yay! I’m glad somebody was nice, at least."
    Marina "Ура! Я рада, что нашелся хоть кто-то добрый."

# game/script/hwb_s15a.rpy:156
translate spanish hwb_s15a_72316380:

    # Amber "Yeah. Still a long way to go, though."
    Amber "Ага. Но впереди еще долгий путь."

# game/script/hwb_s15a.rpy:160
translate spanish hwb_s15a_797fe013:

    # "The long line of cars extends as far as I can see, before it finally goes out of sight around a bend in the road."
    "La larga fila de autos se extiende hasta donde alcanzo a ver, antes de desaparecer de vista en una curva del camino."

# game/script/hwb_s15a.rpy:164
translate spanish hwb_s15a_d3fd13d4:

    # Marina "Why do you think it’s so much busier here than the other places we’ve been?"
    Marina "Как думаешь, почему здесь настолько оживленное движение, относительно других мест, где мы бывали?"

# game/script/hwb_s15a.rpy:168
translate spanish hwb_s15a_c5e29ca8:

    # Amber "Arches is one of the most popular national parks. Like, when you think of parks in the US, you think of Arches and the Grand Canyon and Yosemite. That kind of thing."
    Amber "Арчес один из самых популярных национальных парков. Например, когда ты думаешь о парках в США, ты думаешь об Арчес, Большом Каньоне и Йосемитском парке. Ну или что-то вроде этого."

# game/script/hwb_s15a.rpy:172
translate spanish hwb_s15a_269dc76a:

    # Amber "So I think a lot of people will be at those big spots."
    Amber "Так что, я думаю, что подавляющее большинство людей будет в таких известных местах."

# game/script/hwb_s15a.rpy:174
translate spanish hwb_s15a_eba86a27:

    # Marina "Think it’ll be like Shiprock again?"
    Marina "Думаешь, будет как в Шип Роке?"

# game/script/hwb_s15a.rpy:178
translate spanish hwb_s15a_9f9c91c9:

    # Amber "What, with the megaphone and law enforcement?"
    Amber "Что? С мегафонами и охраной правопорядка?"

# game/script/hwb_s15a.rpy:180
translate spanish hwb_s15a_58e008ea:

    # Marina "Mhm."
    Marina "Угусь."

# game/script/hwb_s15a.rpy:184
translate spanish hwb_s15a_4aed1eba:

    # Amber "Maybe. Probably not. These parks are a lot bigger and more spread out. Way harder to have people watching. Their only option would be to straight up close."
    Amber "Может быть. Но, скорее всего, нет. Эти парки намного больше. Куда труднее нарваться на любопытных наблюдателей. Чтобы что-то разглядеть, им придется подойти в упор."

# game/script/hwb_s15a.rpy:188
translate spanish hwb_s15a_01acdb85:

    # Marina "And then you have horrible people who sneak in or out of bounds anyway."
    Marina "И среди них есть ужасные люди, которые прячутся вне поля зрения и выходят за рамки."

# game/script/hwb_s15a.rpy:192
translate spanish hwb_s15a_3be8313f:

    # Amber "Yeah, exactly. Who would ever do that?"
    Amber "Да, точно. Но кто будет так делать?"

# game/script/hwb_s15a.rpy:196
translate spanish hwb_s15a_fd5248b7:

    # Marina "Nobody we know, that’s for sure."
    Marina "Никто из тех, кого мы знаем, это уж точно."

# game/script/hwb_s15a.rpy:200
translate spanish hwb_s15a_efa024e2:

    # Amber "It’s okay, once we’re filthy rich we can make a donation to the Canyon or something."
    Amber "Все в порядке. Когда мы будем отвратительно богаты, мы сможем внести пожертвование на счет Большого Каньона или типа того."

# game/script/hwb_s15a.rpy:204
translate spanish hwb_s15a_f5006e12:

    # Marina "Let’s just buy the canyon and then pay to have everything reconstructed."
    Marina "Давай просто купим Каньон и оплатим его полное восстановление."

# game/script/hwb_s15a.rpy:208
translate spanish hwb_s15a_8aff6cdf:

    # Amber "Perfect."
    Amber "Идеально."

# game/script/hwb_s15a.rpy:210
translate spanish hwb_s15a_c9641eb9:

    # "It takes a while, but we finally make it past all of the stoplights. After that, it’s still slow going, but at least it’s steady. Maybe fifteen minutes pass crawling through town before things start to pick up."
    "Tarda un rato, pero finalmente logramos pasar todos los semáforos. Después de eso, sigue siendo lento, pero al menos es constante. Pasan como quince minutos arrastrándonos por el pueblo antes de que las cosas empiecen a mejorar."

# game/script/hwb_s15a.rpy:212
translate spanish hwb_s15a_07f72831:

    # "Still a couple miles away, I can finally see the exit for the park itself. Some people continue past, staying on the highway, but most are in line for Arches. At least there’s a whole lane for people like us."
    "Todavía a un par de millas de distancia, finalmente puedo ver la salida hacia el parque. Algunos siguen de largo, quedándose en la autopista, pero la mayoría está en fila para Arches. Al menos hay un carril completo para gente como nosotras."

# game/script/hwb_s15a.rpy:214
translate spanish hwb_s15a_5127a096:

    # "Traffic is congested like my nose in winter, but the end is in sight."
    "El tráfico está congestionado como mi nariz en invierno, pero el final está a la vista."

# game/script/hwb_s15a.rpy:218
translate spanish hwb_s15a_cc130871:

    # Amber "May as well get comfy. We’re gonna be here a while."
    Amber "Располагайся. Нам придется постоять тут какое-то время."

# game/script/hwb_s15a.rpy:220
translate spanish hwb_s15a_944c522a:

    # "Taking my advice, Marina leans back and props her feet up on the dash. Her dress bunches up by her knees, leaving most of her legs exposed."
    "Siguiendo mi consejo, Marina se reclina y apoya los pies en el tablero. Su vestido se arruga cerca de sus rodillas, dejando la mayor parte de sus piernas al descubierto."

# game/script/hwb_s15a.rpy:224
translate spanish hwb_s15a_7e96b3e2:

    # "I sneak a few guilty glances from the corner of my eye. If I didn’t know better, I’d think that all the skin she shows was intentional. But it’s Marina, which means she’s not even conscious about this stuff."
    "Echo algunas miradas culpables de reojo. Si no supiera mejor, pensaría que toda la piel que muestra es intencional. Pero es Marina, lo que significa que ni siquiera es consciente de estas cosas."

# game/script/hwb_s15a.rpy:226
translate spanish hwb_s15a_4689fc60:

    # "Or me, for that matter. I wonder if she knows that I’m… into her."
    "O a mí, para el caso. Me pregunto si sabrá que… me gusta."

# game/script/hwb_s15a.rpy:230
translate spanish hwb_s15a_b3556311:

    # "To distract myself, I grab the box of tapes."
    "Para distraerme, agarro la caja de casetes."

# game/script/hwb_s15a.rpy:232
translate spanish hwb_s15a_4803964f:

    # "I kept the music off earlier so that Marina could sleep."
    "Antes mantuve la música apagada para que Marina pudiera dormir."

# game/script/hwb_s15a.rpy:236
translate spanish hwb_s15a_cb9abd9d:

    # Amber "Wanna pick this time?"
    Amber "Хочешь выбрать сама в этот раз?"

# game/script/hwb_s15a.rpy:240
translate spanish hwb_s15a_5f96a8c4:

    # Marina "Sure."
    Marina "Конечно."

# game/script/hwb_s15a.rpy:246
translate spanish hwb_s15a_a6db68af:

    # "Setting it in her lap, she begins to rummage through the bin."
    "Colocándola en su regazo, comienza a hurgar en el contenedor."

# game/script/hwb_s15a.rpy:248
translate spanish hwb_s15a_b28820cd:

    # "I’m pretty sure that she knows all of the music I have by now. We’ve listened to every tape at least once. And I have an okay feel for what she likes and what she doesn’t."
    "Estoy bastante segura de que ya conoce toda la música que tengo. Hemos escuchado cada casete al menos una vez. Y tengo una idea decente de lo que le gusta y lo que no."

# game/script/hwb_s15a.rpy:250
translate spanish hwb_s15a_71ce0821:

    # "Sometimes she taps her fingers to the beat or hums along when she likes what we’re listening to. If she doesn’t, she flat out ignores it."
    "A veces golpetea los dedos al ritmo o tararea cuando le gusta lo que escuchamos. Si no, lo ignora por completo."

# game/script/hwb_s15a.rpy:252
translate spanish hwb_s15a_52d25d83:

    # "The one she settles on is an album of instrumental folk songs. Very stereotypical western-sounding."
    "El que elige es un álbum de canciones folclóricas instrumentales. Suena muy típico del oeste."

# game/script/hwb_s15a.rpy:254
translate spanish hwb_s15a_c7a53559:

    # "It's a little high-energy for just sitting still in traffic, but that's alright. It's better than nothing."
    "Es un poco enérgico para estar sentada sin hacer nada en el tráfico, pero está bien. Es mejor que nada."

# game/script/hwb_s15a.rpy:256
translate spanish hwb_s15a_5df57eb8:

    # "We just listen to the music, which I’ve cranked up loud, while we wait. The album is nearly half over by the time we finally make it through the park gates."
    "Solo escuchamos la música, que he subido de volumen, mientras esperamos. El álbum está casi a la mitad cuando finalmente pasamos por las puertas del parque."

